summary:
I wish to be a part of many individuals journey of personal growth, and watch others become knowledgeable of their strengths and use them to the best of their ability. 

My personal goals are, and always have been, associated with assisting/supporting and guiding others. 

I have very confidently held mental health workshops at schools, informing and encouraging individuals about their future.

I have taken part in a lot of community service and voluntary work - which I find incredibly rewarding. 

Services ready and wishing to provide as a result of experience:

- Mental health and wellbeing.
- counselling/psychotherapeutic services with supervision 
- workplace environment/change management 
- acknowledgment & enhancement of personal strengths 

- i have completed my undergraduate degree in applied social sciences with distinctions (78%)
- i have completed postgraduate honours in academic psychology - with distinction
- accepted to 3 UK universities for my masters and requested to apply for my Doctorate/PhD as a result of my academics and experience.
